Text: Seeing that moon makes me remember.

Why am I still wearing a uniform even though I'm
over twenty...?
I am. I can't abandon my friends.
the least I can do...is bring back their stuff.

(There was a boy I hated. He was a C student who was
unremarkable at sports.)

(With ordinary looks, he was completely forgettable.
And yet―)

(Seeing that moon makes me remember. About that
day.)

(I knew it. There's no way a human attacked by them
could survive for several days.)
I'm sorry for taking my time...
When was the last time I was alone...?
but there's no one behind her.
Surviving can be such dirty work...
Standing before her is a large muscular man.

When Akane opens her eyes, she finds herself in a
dimly lit warehouse.
Apparently, it seals a knight's powers.

You shouldn't walk alone at night, even if you're
the Savior. Who knows? You might get caught up
with some bad people.

Our client wants your life. Seems like you've made
quite the enemy, Savior.

They said they wanted to kill you with their own
hands, so we're to hand you over alive.
Such a luxury in these times...

Calm down, Dek! We'll get plenty of drugs after we
deal with her!

Sorry, Savior. Both me and this guy, our minds are
messed up pretty badly.
Kill! Must kill! Or he'll... He'll...aaaaah!!!
Can't even remember who I am, or what I used to do.
Ngh! Can't get him out of my head! I can't...

She hears footsteps behind her. Click, click, click.
Someone is coming closer.

A moonlit night, amidst kidnappers—Akane suddenly
recalls a scene from her past.
The kidnapper pounces on the man like a beast.

But the man instantly sends the kidnapper flying
through the air.
